<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Government Accused for Filing False Case Against  Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Bangladesh
Nationalist Party ( BNP) Wednesday accused the government of Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina of filing "false" case against its chief
Begum Khaleda Zia only to tarnish her image ahead of the national
election next year.
</P>
<P>
At a public rally here Wednesday, they said the BNP Chairperson
and former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia was falsely implicated in a
graft case Tuesday, only a few days after another opposition
leader was convicted by a high court bench.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the rally held by the four-party opposition alliance,
Sadek Hossain Khoka, president of Dhaka City Chapter of BNP, said
the case was filed by the government "just to destroy the
popularity of our leader."
</P>
<P>
The Bureau of Anti-Corruption on Tuesday submitted a charge-
sheet in a court of Dhaka accusing Khaleda Zia, her two cabinet
colleagues and eight officials for embezzlement of 34.8 million U.
S. dollars in purchase of two Airbuses in 1994 while she was in
power.
</P>
<P>
Two ministers of Khaleda Zia are former Finance Minister Saifur
Rahman and Civil Aviation Minister Major (Ret) Abdul Mannan.
</P>
<P>
The BNP chief has also been accused in another corruption case
involving nearly 120,000 dollars for decorating her Dhaka Garrison
residence while she was in power from 1991-1996.
</P>
<P>
Political observers here believed that Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina is in a bid to destroy the popularity of the opposition
leaders before the general election next year.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that the investigation of the case was
completed two years ago, but the government kept in hand only to
use it at an appropriate time to belittle Khaleda's popularity
before the national election in a bid to reap maximum political
dividends.
</P>
<P>
On August 24, Jatiya Party Chairman and former President Ershad
was sentenced by a high court bench for five years in prison and
fined nearly one million U.S. dollars on graft charges.
</P>
<P>
Political observers here said that since Ershad's Jatiya Party
is one of the main partners of the opposition alliance, the case
of the former president was accelerated to destabilize the four-
party alliance led by BNP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
