<HEADLINE> Taliban Captures Taloqan Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Taliban militia of
Afghanistan Wednesday evening captured Taloqan airport and Bharak
district, an important key position of the opposition forces,
without any resistance, according to a report from the Afghan
Islamic Press (AIP).
</P>
<P>
Taloqan airport is situated at a distance of five to six
kilometers north of the main city Taloqan, main base of the
opposition Northern Alliance forces in northern parts of the
country.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban militia, which captured Taloqan earlier in the day
after fierce fighting, faced no resistance in capturing the
airport.
</P>
<P>
Taliban forces, after heavy fighting, entered the northwestern
Bharak district and also captured Qayum bazar.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban forces are strengthening their positions on the
suburb of Taloqan city. However, according to another report, the
opposition forces have blown up an important bridge in Tangi
Kharkhar, 15 kilometers off Taloqan, to stop the Taliban forces'
advance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
