<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peacekeeping Operations Must Observe U.N. Charter: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said Thursday that it is essential to treat symptoms and remove
the root causes that lead to conflicts at the same time in order
to enable U.N. peacekeeping operations to work better.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made these remarks here when addressing the U.N. Security
Council Summit which was held today as part of the three-day UN
Millennium Summit that opened on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that peacekeeping operations constitute one of the
major means by which the United Nations fulfills its
responsibility for the maintenance of international peace and
security.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations should sum up its past experience and
lessons," Jiang said. "It is true that the peacekeeping operations
have contributed to international peace and security. But they are
not a panacea."
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that facts have proven that the success of the U.
N. peacekeeping operations depends on observance of the purposes
and principles of the U.N. Charter, particularly the principles of
respect for state sovereignty, non-interference in the internal
affairs of the recipient countries, seeking prior consent of the
parties concerned, neutrality, and non-use of force except for
self-defense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
