hamper their ability to compete with international companies."
</P>
<P>
Despite the prediction that e-commerce growth in the Arab Gulf
region is expected to reach up to 3 billion U.S. dollars by the
year 2003, this is a small figure in comparison with 1.3 trillion
dollars in the international market.
</P>
<P>
The warning comes just one month before the official opening of
Dubai Internet City, the first electronic free Zone of its kind in
the world, and it can offer companies 100 percent foreign ownership
and 50 year renewable leases, according to the report. 
