<HEADLINE> Memorial Services Held in Greece for Earthquake Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Greece Thursday conducted
memorial services for the victims of the catastrophic earthquake
that hit Athens on September 7 last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 143 people were killed and thousands of others
injured and hundreds of houses were also destroyed in the
earthquake measuring 5.9 on the Richter scale. The epicenter was
in the Mount Parnitha region, some 20 kilometers northwest of the
Greek capital.
</P>
<P>
The Greek government announced recently that the cost of the
earthquake would rise to 900 billion drachmas (about 2.37 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, in churches throughout the quake-striken area such
as Menidi, Metamorphosi, Ano Liosia, Anthoupoli and at the ruins
of the Ricomex factory building that claimed the lives of 40
people, emotional scenes were being played out at memorial
services for the dead.
</P>
<P>
The services were attended by Greek environment and Town
Planning Minister Costas Laliotis, Transport and Communications
Minister Christos Verelis, a representative of the Greek President
Costis Stephanopoulos and other government officials.
</P>
<P>
The services ended with a minute's silence in memory of the
victims, after which the Greek government delegation visited
nearby camps and were briefed on the problems facing earthquake
victims living there.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, acting Greek government spokesman Telemachos Hytiris
expressed the government's sorrow to the relatives of the
earthquake victims.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government would make full restitution to the
earthquake victims and a special government meeting to discuss the
issues would be held as soon as Greek Prime Minister Costas
Simitis returned from New York where he is currently taking part
in the U.N. Millennium Summit.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Vasilis Papazachos, a professor at
the Thessaloniki's Aristotle University, said Thursday that the
Athens earthquake which was not that strong to cause so many
victims was an additional motivation for the intensification of
the research concerning the earthquake prediction.
</P>
<P>
He said that it would soon be possible to say if a medium-term
earthquake prediction was possible.
</P>
<P>
The professor was optimistic that the prediction of earthquakes
two years before they occur, their magnitude and their epicenter
with a proximity of 60 kilometers would be possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
