<HEADLINE> OECD, China to Organize Investment Conference in Southern Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development (OECD) and the Chinese government will
co-sponsor on September 11 and 12 a conference on foreign
investment in China in the southern Chinese city of Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
OECD said in a communique on Thursday that the conference,
entitled "Current Challenges of Foreign Direct Investment in China,
" will be attended by over 100 senior officials and executives
from OECD countries, Chinese government, business and investment
groups, international organizations, and research institutes.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of the conference includes discussion of "
the driving forces and economic effects of foreign direct
investment on China's development and future plans and policies of
foreign direct investment," and "exchange of information and
experiences on best foreign investment promotion practices," said
the Paris-based group.
</P>
<P>
This will be the second major event organized by OECD and the
Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation under a
program launched a year ago to develop a common approach to
analyze foreign investment trends and its impact in China and to
enhance policy dialogue, it said. 
</P>
