<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Top Legislator Begins Visit to Estonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TALLINN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
arrived here on Thursday to start a three-day official visit to
Estonia, the first by a top Chinese legislator.
</P>
<P>
In a written airport speech, Li Peng said that during his stay
here, he will have discussions with Estonian leaders on how to
further develop the friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to meet Estonian President Lennart Meri,
Parliament Speaker Toomas Savi and other Estonian leaders and
exchange views on bilateral ties and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Li wound up his official visit to Belarus and left Minsk, the
capital city, Thursday afternoon before arriving in Tallinn.
</P>
</TEXT>
