<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, September 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The U.N. Security Council on Wednesday
condemned the killing of three U.N. staffs by Indonesian militia,
urging the Indonesian Government to take measures to end violence
in West Timor where East Timor refugees remain.
</P>
<P>
At an urgent meeting called after the incident occurred
Wednesday at Atambua of West Timor, the council reiterated its
concern about militia activity in the region and militia
incursions into U.N.-administered East Timor, which led to the
death of two U.N. peacekeepers earlier this summer, according to
council president, Mali's Moctar Ouane.
</P>
<P>
Confirming the murder of the three staffs of the U.N. High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) by the militiamen against
independence of East Timor, U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
described the security situation in West Timor as "unacceptable".
(U.N.-West Timor-Condemn)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israel's acting Foreign Minister Shlomo Ben-Ami
Thursday urged Prime Minister Ehud Barak and Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat to make final decisions on an Israeli-Palestinian
peace accord.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on Israel Radio after reports from New York earlier
Thursday showed that U.S. President Bill Clinton failed to break
the deadlock in the peace process, Ben-Ami said "This is no longer
time for negotiations, it's a time for decisions by leaders."
</P>
<P>
Barak and Arafat are both in New York to attend the United
Nations Millennium Summit. They met Clinton separately, the first
meetings since their summit at Camp David last July ended without
an agreement. (Israel-Palesine-Peace)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Union (EU) on Thursday complained
about the further devaluation of the euro, which kept hitting
record lows in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
"The exchange rate does not reflect the real value of the euro
and contradicts with all the data concerning the EU growth in the
first six months of the year," said Gerassimos Thomas, an official
of the European Commission, the executive body of the 15-nation
bloc.
</P>
<P>
The single currency went as low as 86.35 cents against the
dollar on Thursday and there seemed to be no immediate brake to
stop the free-falling. (EU-Euro-Devaluation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW YORK -- The Interactive Round-Table session of the
Millennium Summit of the United Nations was held in the U.N.
headquarters on Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin attended the session and will
deliver a speech on the role of the United Nations, economic
globalization and the relationship between human rights and
sovereignty. (U.N.-Jiang-Round-table Session) 
