<HEADLINE> Cyprus Rally 2000 to Open on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The curtain of the Cyprus
Rally 2000 will open on Friday in Limassol, a southwestern coastal
town on the Cyprus island, it was reported here.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Rally, which is the tenth of the fourteen round
World Rally Championship, is for the first time included in the
calendar of the FIA's (International Automobile Federation) World
Championship.
</P>
<P>
The Limassol based Rally will begin in the morning of September
8 and is organized by the Cyprus Automobile Association.
</P>
<P>
Six manufacturers teams have entered the Rally. They are:
Mitsubishi, Ford, Subaru, Peugeot, Seat and Skoda.
</P>
<P>
In those teams are all the drivers at the top of the World
Championship leader board with names such as Marcus Gronholm, who
currently is in the lead of the Championship, Richard Burns, Colin
McRae, Carlos Sainz and Tommi Makkinen.
</P>
<P>
During the race the cars will do nine special stages totaling
145 kilometers in the first of three legs. Leg two will comprise
eight special stages totalling 115 kilometers and the final leg
will cover six stages with total distance of 88 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Currently Marcus Gronholm of Peugeot leads the World Driver's
Championship with 44 points, followed by Richard Burns of Subaru
with 38 points. Colin McRae and Carlos Sainz of Ford and Tommi
Makinen of Mitsubishi complete the first five leading drivers.
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus Rally 2000 will finish on Sunday afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
