<HEADLINE> Ethiopians to Compete in Race, Boxing in Sydney Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Olympic
Committee has announced that its sportsmen will compete in long-
distance running and boxing items in the forthcoming Sydney
Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
Of the race items that Ethiopian sportsmen have chosen include
women's marathon, men's marathon, women's 10,000 meters, men's 10,
000 meters, men's 5,000 meters, women's 5,000 meters, men's 1,500
meters, women's 1,500 meters and 3,000 meters steeplechase.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-seven people of the 53-member Ethiopian delegation,
including well-known long-distance runner Haile G.Selassie and
Gete Wami, will participate in the above-mentioned competition
items.
</P>
<P>
In addition, three Ethiopians will take part in the competition
of boxing at 57kg, 60kg and 67kg categories.
</P>
<P>
The name list of the Ethiopian competitors follows:
</P>
<P>
Women's Marathon
</P>
<P>
