<HEADLINE> S. African President to Visit Nigeria for 40th Anniversary of Independence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki will be the guest of honor at the celebrations marking
Nigeria's 40th anniversary of independence, the South African
Press Association reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki will pay a three-day visit to the most populous African
country at the end of this month during which he will meet
President Olusegun Obasanjo and attend the October 1 Independence
Day celebrations, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The visit -- the exact dates of which have yet to be announced -
-will be just the latest in a series of exchanges between the two
countries after an improvement in bilateral relations since the
military rule in Nigeria was ended last year.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria had been a prominent supporter of the fight against
apartheid in South Africa before the latter achieved black
majority rule in 1994, but their relations remained strained under
the Nigerian regime of late military ruler Sani Abacha with the
South African government a leading critic of the regime.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have set up a joint trade commission since
Nigeria returned to civilian rule last May. They have also held
regular talks underlining their claims to a leadership role in the
continent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
