<HEADLINE> Chinese Newspapers Keen on Environmental Protection Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese newspapers cover more
articles on environmental protection than before, according to a
survey released today by a non-governmental environmental
organization "Friends of Nature."
</P>
<P>
The organization surveyed 75 newspapers, which published 47,000
pieces of news stories on the environment in 1999, or two such
stories in one newspapers each day, compared with one story every
two days in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The newspapers devoted a large space to problems on wildlife
protection and air and water pollution last year. However, three
years ago, more environmental reporting was about tree planting,
sanitation and government-advocated environmental campaigns.
</P>
<P>
"Friends of Nature" started in 1994 to conduct the annual
survey and evaluation.
</P>
<P>
Volunteers with the organization said that newspapers play an
important role in improving public awareness on environmental
protection. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
