<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhongshan University Sets Up Campus in Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Zhongshan University, in
this capital south China's Guangdong Province, has set up a campus
in Zhuhai city in the same province.
</P>
<P>
Some 4,200 freshmen started their first university semester
today at the campus in Zhuhai, one of the country's earliest
special economic zones, said a local education official.
</P>
<P>
Established by Zhongshan University and the Zhuhai city
government, the campus is a new approach in university education
in China, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The 76-year old Zhongshan University has thus become the
country's first institute of higher education with campuses in
different cities, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Zhuhai government gave 3.4 square kilometers of land for
the facility, along with 100 million yuan in funding for a
classroom building and teaching equipment.
</P>
<P>
Zhongshan University will also spend large sum of investment
for its Zhuhai campus, which will create a college for oceanic
studies, tourism management and research centers.
</P>
<P>
So far, a 776,000-square-meters classroom building with 179
classrooms has been set up on the campus. Other education and
living facilities such as library, a dormitory, a dining hall and
a service center have also been built.
</P>
<P>
Zhongshan University has a postgraduate research institute and
12 colleges where nearly 20,000 students are receiving higher
education. 
</P>
</TEXT>
