<HEADLINE> State Councilor Wu Yi Meets Hong Kong Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua)-- The Chinese central government
is happy to note that Hong Kong has so far cast off the negative
influence of the Asian financial crisis and realized an overall
recovery, said State Councilor Wu Yi here today.
</P>
<P>
Wu made this remark during a meeting with delegates from the
Hong Kong industrial and commercial circle participating the
upcoming fourth China Investment and Trade Fair, which is
scheduled in this special economic zone of east China's Fujian
Province from September 8-12.
</P>
<P>
Such a success of Hong Kong is achieved under the leadership of
the Hong Kong SAR government headed by Chief Executive Tung Chee-
Hwa and by sticking to the principle of one country, two systems,
Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong, and a high degree of
autonomy, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
She expressed gladness over meeting old friends again and
making acquaintances with new friends as well. She spoke highly of
Hong Kong's active participation to the economic development of
the mainland, expressing the hope that concerted efforts would
continue for the common prosperity of the country.
</P>
<P>
The annual fair, the only national activity aimed to lure
direct overseas funds, is sponsored by the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation, the Fujian Provincial People's
Government and the Xiamen City People's Government.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the fair is expected to combine investment with trade,
presentation with negotiations, project promotion with policy
consultation, business activities with academic discussions.
</P>
<P>
She also voiced the hope that delegates present would take this
opportunity to learn more about the mainland so as to participate
more in its economic construction.
</P>
<P>
The delegates expressed their common wish that economic and
trade ties between Hong Kong and the mainland would be further
expanded. 
</P>
