<HEADLINE> State Councilor Meets Thai Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 7 (Xinhua)-- Chinese State Councilor Wu Yi
met here today with deputy Prime Minister of Thailand Supachai
Panitchpakdi and his party, who are here to attend the 4th China
Investment and Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Wu said the Chinese and Thai peoples enjoy traditional
friendship, adding that the two countries have established a good-
neighborly and mutual trusting relations after the two countries
forged diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
She said the Sino-Thai relationship has become a model for
state-to-state relations. The two countries should cherish all the
more their relations, the State Councilor stressed.
</P>
<P>
Wu congratulated Supachai for his upcoming post as director-
general of the World Trade Organization (WTO). She said that China
will support Supachai's work in the organization.
</P>
<P>
On the WTO, Wu said more demands of the developing countries
should be taken into consideration in the upcoming round of
multilateral talks.
</P>
<P>
Trade talks should not include those issues that ought to be
tackled by other international organizations, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Supachai told Wu that he is glad to see the process of China's
entry into the WTO is almost over, adding that he believes China
can finish the work to enter the WTO by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Taken the economic scale of China, Supachai said, China will
surely play an important role in the WTO.
</P>
<P>
He said the future WTO should be democratic, equal, and
transparent
</P>
<P>
Supachai thanked China for its support to Thailand during the
Asian financial crisis. 
</P>
