<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urged to Curb Spread of AIDs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Alarmed at the fact that AIDs
is spreading at a fast pace in China, top government advisors
today called for redoubled efforts in curbing the fatal disease
and promoting greater public awareness.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting of the Counselors Office of the State Council,
these advisors also urged the media to play a larger role in
spreading the knowledge on the threat of the deadly disease.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, a special law on the prevention of AIDs/HIV should
be issued to make clear the duties of the government and different
social groups in combating AIDs.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Health, the first AIDs patient was
detected in 1981, and now the total number of AIDs patients and
HIV carriers reached 34.3 million worldwide.
</P>
<P>
In China, AIDs infections have been reported in all the
provinces, municipalities and autonomous regions, with the
official figure standing at 18,000. Sixty percent of the victims
are aged between 18-39 years.
</P>
<P>
Local experts have demanded crackdown on prostitution and drug
addiction and trafficking as people involved in the illegal trades
are vulnerable to the deadly virus. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
