<HEADLINE> China on Alert of Typhoon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Central Meteorological
Station today released an alarm against the advent of a typhoon.
</P>
<P>
This year's No. 16 tropical storm, named Wukong in Chinese, was
centralized at 18.9 degrees north latitude and 115.4 degrees east
longitude at 5 p.m. Beijing Time.
</P>
<P>
The center of the typhoon, heading for the east sea area of
China's southernmost province of Hainan, is estimated to move at a
speed of 10 to 15 kilometers per hour. The typhoon is expected to
land on Hainan tomorrow night or the day after tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Under the influence of the typhoon, strong gale and rain storms
will hit South China Sea and the coastal area of south China's
Guangdong Province from tonight to tomorrow. 
</P>
</TEXT>
