<HEADLINE> 37 Die in Floods in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Peou Samy, secretary general of the NCDM said in the statement
that the damage caused by the second flood amounted to 3 million U.
S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He has appealed to foreign donors to help the affected people.
"NCDM has an honor to appeal foreign embassies, donor countries, U.
N. agencies, NON-government organizations, and international
organizations to provide assistance to the Royal Government of
Cambodia in kind and cash so as to assist the people affected both
from the first Mekong flood and the current flood," he said.
</P>
<P>
The recent two floods had left a total of 52 people dead, 942
houses destroyed, according to the report of the National
Committee for Disaster Management (NCDM).
</P>
<P>
In the past few days, the government declared the state of
emergency to all residents living along the Mekong river.
</P>
<P>
Up to Thursday, the water level was down a little bit, although
in Phnom Penh the water level is still alarming. But water experts
said that Phnom Penh will not be flooded.
</P>
<P>
The current water level is 10.74 meters, and Phnom Penh will be
flooded if it reached 11.2 meters. 
</P>
