<HEADLINE> Nigerian House Requests Probe of Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's House of
Representatives has requested the Auditor-general of the
Federation to conduct a comprehensive audit of the finances of the
three arms of the government.
</P>
<P>
The house asked, in a resolution passed on Wednesday, the
Auditor-general to conduct the audit within the shortest possible
time and submit its report to the National Assembly, Nigerian
press reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In an apparent response to the decision, the Federal Executive
Council, the highest executive body of the government, said that
ministers were not afraid of the probes.
</P>
<P>
A probe last month found shocking corruption in the country's
senate, upper chamber of the top legislature, and the senate
leadership stepped down as a result. 
</P>
