<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Electrical Problems -- Main Causes for Fire Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Liu Ruixiang, director of the
Beijing Fire Control Administration, said today 28 percent of fire
accidents in the city last year were due to electrical problems.
</P>
<P>
Liu said old power grids, defects in electrical design, and
residents' improper use of electricity have been the main causes
for fires. Fire accidents caused by electricity last year numbered
over 1,350, and in the first half of this year over 700, or 26.8
percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Liu said it is high time to publicize information on the
correct use of electricity and to intensify government control in
electricity.
</P>
<P>
Specialists are required to be certified to use electric
facilities and machinery involved in construction and decoration.
Routine tests will be given on the implementation of related laws
and regulations involving the use of electricity and preventing
electrical fires. 
</P>
</TEXT>
