<HEADLINE> China-Belarus Cooperation Sees Promising Prospects (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China-Belarus relations have
been developing remarkably thanks to joint efforts, thus laying a
solid foundation for their cooperation in economic, trade,
scientific, technological and military fields.
</P>
<P>
The remarks came today from Belarus's ambassador to China
Vladimir Rusakevich in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
He said bilateral relations based on goodwill, equality and
mutual benefit have gone well since the establishment of
diplomatic relations in 1992, adding that the two countries have
had similar views and supported each other on many international
issues.
</P>
<P>
He added that Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of
China's National People's Congress (NPC), is visiting Belarus at
this moment, as a result, exchanges between parliaments of the two
countries have been increased and areas of cooperation expanded.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao also paid a
successful visit to Belarus not long ago, where leaders of the two
countries discussed "bilateral relations and international issues
of common concern" in a friendly, down-to-earth and constructive
manner.
</P>
<P>
"Frequent contacts between leaders of the two countries have
set the direction for bilateral economic and trade cooperation,"
he said.
</P>
