<HEADLINE> FIFA Confirms 2002 World Cup Final in Yokohama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The final of the 2002 World Cup
Soccer tournament will be staged in Yokohama, Japan on June 30,
FIFA confirmed on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 64 matches in the tournament will be split evenly between
South Korea and Japan with 10 venues in each country.
</P>
<P>
In South Korea they are Busan, Daegu, Incheon, Gwangju, Daejeon,
Ulsan, Suwon, Jeonju and Seogwipo. In Japan matches will be played
in Yokohama, Sapporo, Miyagi, Niigata, Ibaraki, Saitama, Shizuoka,
Osaka, Kobe and Oita.
</P>
<P>
Three kick-off times will be used throughout the tournament, 3.
30pm, 6pm and 8.30pm (local time).
</P>
<P>
With the exception of June 2 (and the days on which the final
group matches are played), no more than three matches will be
played on any one day.
</P>
<P>
The kick-offs on June 2 have been timed so that the afternoon
matches will be played at 2.30pm in Saitama (Japan) and 4.30pm in
Busan (South Korea) with the evening matches at 6.30pm in Ibaraki
(Japan) and 8.30pm in Gwangju (South Korea).
</P>
<P>
South Korea will play their first match on June 4 in Busan
followed by fixtures in Daegu (June 10) and Incheon (June 14).
</P>
<P>
Co-hosts Japan will also start on June 4 in Saitama before
matches in Yokohama (June 9) and Osaka (June 14). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
