<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Dragged Lower by Tech Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed
nearly one percent lower Thursday, dragged down by tech stocks
following a sell-off in the U.S. technology sector.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip Hang Seng Index shed 173.28 points, or 0.98
percent, to close at 17,431.95, on a turnover of 11.46 billion HK
dollars (1.46 billion U.S. dollars), compared with 8.304 billion
HK dollars (1.065 billion U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the four Hang Seng sub-index, Finance gained 0.06 percent
while Utilities, Properties and Commerce &AMP; Industry declined by 0.
09 percent, 2.02 percent and 1.38 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index dropped 0.85 percent to
510.33 while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index went down 1.
05 percent to 1,371.07.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index went down 1.72 percent to 2,801.58 and
Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index down 2.33 percent to 3,372.84.
</P>
</TEXT>
