<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Earthquake Rocks Bengkulu, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A mild earthquake measuring 4.
7 on the Richter scale jolted Bengkulu, capital of Bengkulu
Province,Indonesia, early Thursday morning, but no casualties were
reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was located 33 kilometers beneath
the Indian Ocean or some 153 kilometers west of the Enggano island.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the Bengkulu area was rocked by four earthquakes,
which measured 5.3, 5.1, 5.6 and 4 respectively on the Richter
scale. All of them were located beneath the Indian Ocean and no
casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the quakes were aftershocks of the strong
earthquake which measured 7.8 on the Richter scale and rocked
Bengkulu last June. The quake killed more than 100 people and
injured hundreds of others.
</P>
<P>
Almost 3,000 aftershocks were recorded after the strong quake,
97 of which were felt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
