<HEADLINE> Thailand Offers Medical Aid to Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Rural Ear, Nose and
Throat Foundation of Thailand and Rajavithi Hospital, in
cooperation with the Ministry of Public Health and Ministry of
Foreign Affairs of Thailand, will conduct an Ear Surgery Mobile
Unit Project in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The project, announced at a news briefing here Thursday by Thai
Ambassador to Cambodia Asiphol Chabchitrchaidol, is to be held
between September 2 and 11 and will bring a total of 16 Thai
medical doctors to perform examinations and operations and give
medication and hearing tests to Cambodians free of charge.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of the mission is to contribute to technical
cooperation among developing countries by giving free medical
services to the Cambodian people, alleviate or decrease deafness
or hearing impairment and build awareness about deafness among the
public and authorities concerned. 
</P>
