<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Siemens Negotiating for Stakes in Malaysian IT Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Siemens Malaysia Sdn Bhd
is currently in negotiation to acquire stakes in four local small
and medium companies in the information technology (IT) related
field through its venture capital investment exercise.
</P>
<P>
The company started discussions with the companies a month ago
and"we will be investing some 5 to 6 million ringgit in each
company if the outcome is positive," Felix Heinimann, the company'
s vice president in charge of strategic marketing and corporate
communications, said Thursday without naming the companies.
</P>
<P>
Siemens Malaysia plans to take on only minority stakes in these
companies, Heinimann told reporters after a briefing on the launch
of the Siemens Information and Communication Mobile Business
Campaign.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that Siemens Malaysia had proposed the setting up
of a locally based venture capital company to fund start-up
companies in the country and said this venture capital company is
to later cater to ventures around Asia.
</P>
<P>
On the six-month campaign, he said the campaign is aimed at
boosting awareness about mobile business among Malaysians and at
positioning Siemens Malaysia as one of the top five global
information and communication service providers by 2003.
</P>
<P>
He said the success of many companies will depend on how
quickly and effectively they make their business mobile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
