<HEADLINE> French Chemical Company Sets up Joint Venture in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- France's chemical company Rhodia
will set up a joint venture of rare earths in China to develop
high-tech products for electronic, automotive, chemical and glass
markets, said Rhodia in a communique on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rhodia, which is one of the world leaders in specialty
chemicals, will set up the Liyang Rhodia Founder Rare Earth New
Material Company with Beijing Founder Group and Liyang Licheng
Economic General Industrial Company in eastern Jiangsu province.
</P>
<P>
Rhodia said that it will hold 45 percent of the shares in the
joint venture, which will produce products for overseas as well as
domestic markets in China.
</P>
<P>
Through this venture, China is expected to become a key
location for manufacturing rare earth products of Rhodia, it said.
</P>
