<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss Army's Strategic Intelligence Unit to Become Civilian Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Swiss President and Defense
Minister Adolf Ogi has announced that Switzerland's strategic
intelligence unit is to be taken out of the army's hands and
transformed into a civilian organization.
</P>
<P>
Ogi, quoted by Thursday's local press reports, said that the
change would take effect from 2001. But he said the army and air
force would retain their own intelligence units.
</P>
<P>
The new civilian body will remain affiliated to the defense
ministry, but will no longer be directly controlled by it, Ogi was
quoted as telling reporters Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision follows a review of the unit's operations in the
wake of last year's fraud scandal. Making the strategic
intelligence unit a civilian body was one of the recommendations
of a report on the secret services, published last February.
</P>
<P>
The report was prompted by the Bellasi affair, named after the
former intelligence officer, Dino Bellasi, who was last year found
to have embezzled nine million Swiss francs (about five million U.
S. dollars) of Defense Ministry funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000907.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Starts to Investigate Accident at Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- In order to investigate the
cause behind a recent mishap during which three workers were
killed and another three people were seriously injured, three
teams have been sent down to the construction site of the Three
Gorges Project.
</P>
<P>
The teams will investigate the general condition of casualties,
equipment and technology, and the handling of the case.
</P>
<P>
Around 6:50 pm on September 3, workers from Gezhouba Company
Group were still working at the flood discharge section of the
gigantic water control dam when the No.3 tower belt machine broke
from the height of 19.6 meters and collapsed, throwing down 29
workers who were working on the belt. Four other workers that were
working below the belt did not escape the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the accident, representatives from Yangtze
River Three Gorges Project Development Corporation, Gezhouba Group
Company, and officials from relevant departments in Yichang, the
nearest city to the construction site, went to the site of the
accident in an effort to rescue workers and preserve evidence.
</P>
<P>
The three seriously injured workers, who have been operated on,
are still in a critical state, while workers that sustained light
injuries in the accident are being kept at a local hospital for
further medical checkups.
</P>
<P>
To avoid further accidents, Gezhouba Group Company has banned
the use of tower belt machines and roof belt machines, while
concrete pouring at the flood discharge section has also
temporarily been stopped, said a corporate spokesman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000907.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
