<HEADLINE> China Hosts Seminar on Insurance, Risk Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Over 20 foreign specialists
and more than 150 Chinese experts gathered in Nankai University
today to attend a three-day seminar on insurance, actuary and risk
management in Tianjin, the largest port city in north China.
</P>
<P>
Organizers with Nankai University said the seminar aims to
intensify exchanges of domestic actuaries with the foreign experts,
thus pushing China's insurance industry towards specialization and
globalization.
</P>
<P>
Norm Crowder, chairman of the North America Actuarial
Association, said the organization established a cooperative
relationship with the university in 1988 in actuaries training.
</P>
<P>
Most of China's 30 actuaries with international certificates
and 43 actuaries with domestic certificates received their
vocational training at the university. 
</P>
