<HEADLINE> Shanghai A Shares Rebounds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
closed at 1950.66 points Thursday, up 24.75 points or 1.29 percent
from the last close.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 7.43 billion yuan, against 8.73 billion yuan
on Wednesday, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line
financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Despite the slump in the previous session, the Shanghai A-
shares opened higher today as investors resumed calmness.
</P>
<P>
Active trading of blue chips and shares held by big players
helped push the market higher.
</P>
<P>
As two companies issued new A-shares on the market today and
another issue is coming on Friday, the market is likely to test
the five-day average line of 1970 points on the last trading day
of the week.
</P>
<P>
Among the shares seeing the largest gain, Shanghai Albatronics
Co. Ltd rose ten percent to close at the day's ceiling of 17.6
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Feilo Acoustics Co. Ltd fell as investors cashed in their
profits, dropping 6.02 percent to 30.92 yuan. 
