<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar dropped
further Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the close the Australian dollar was at 56.42 U.S. cents,
from 56.65 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The currency had fallen during the day to 55.95 U.S. cents, its
weakest point since August 28, 1998, and then rebounded sharply.
</P>
<P>
A bank currency strategist said trading was characterized by
nervous dealings and choppy movements.
</P>
<P>
Australian Prime Minister John Howard reportedly said Wednesday
that the reason for the Australian dollar's dive was a too strong
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
