<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket
closed lower for the third consecutive day Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The All Ordinaries Index finished 15.3 points weaker at 3,266.4
while the S&AMP;P/ASX200 dropped 14.6 points to 3,306.6.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 595.6 million shares worth 1.6 billion
Australian dollars (904 million U.S. dollars). Falling stocks
outnumbered rising ones 892 to 613, with 514 steady.
</P>
<P>
Telstra's shares climbed 16 cents to 6.31 Australian dollars.
Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus edged 2.6 cents higher to 4.326 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Most of the media stocks fell. News Corp's ordinary shares
surrendered 85 cents to 23.5 Australian dollars and its preferred
scrip dived 95 cents to 19.95 dollars. PBL closed 25 cents lower
at 14.4 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the resources sector, BHP picked up 25 cents to 19.61
Australian dollars, Woodside Petroleum jumped 17 cents to 14.38
Australian dollars but Rio Tinto eased 1.7 cents to 26.88
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the banking sector, the Commonwealth added 10 cents to 26.86
Australian dollars, NAB gained 4.9 cents to 25.329 Australian
dollars and ANZ was up 5 cents to 13.15 Australian dollars.
Westpac fell 5.2 cents to 12.708 Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
