<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Can Only Join WTO as China's Separate Customs Territory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China today reiterated its
stance that Taiwan can join the World Trade Organization (WTO)
only as a separate customs territory of China.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi told a press conference
that the Chinese government has held a consistent and clear-cut
stance on Taiwan's entry into the WTO, adding that "We oppose
Taiwan authorities' attempts to create 'two Chinas' or 'one China,
one Taiwan' in multilateral and bilateral areas by taking
advantage of WTO."
</P>
<P>
He said that all parties should adhere to the principles of the
1992 presidential statement of the General Agreement on Tariffs
and Trade (GATT), the former body of the WTO.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the United States will continue to observe the
three Sino-U.S. joint communiques and the three-no commitment on
the related issue," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
