"The army had foiled the LRA rebel plan to raid Kitgum town
suburbs, and in the latest skirmishes, UPDF (the Uganda People's
Defense Forces) inflicted heavy injuries on the rebels," said
Richard Kiwanuka, a brigade commander of the UPDF.
</P>
