<HEADLINE> 37 Feared Drowned in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-seven people were
feared drowned after their overloaded canoe capsized during a
storm on Lake Albert, the police confirmed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The canoe was carrying about 50 people and 120 loads of dried
fish when the storm struck at around 8:00 p.m. local time on
Monday, said Police Spokesman Asumani Mugenyi.
</P>
<P>
"A rescue team of both local people and the police rescued 13
people who were rushed to a dispensary," said Mugenyi.
</P>
<P>
The rescue operation was continuing and 15 bodies had been
recovered so far, he said, adding: "The cause is believed to have
been strong wind but overloading can't be ruled out." 
</P>
