<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nikkei Falls for Eighth Straight Day in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Share prices closed mixed in
Tokyo Thursday, with the benchmark Nikkei index closing for the
eighth straight trading day on declines of high-tech issues.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 99.41 points, or 0.61
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 16,300.46.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX) which covers
all First Section issues, however, marked its first upturn in
eight trading days, rising 2.05 points or 0.14 percent to 1,486.29.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section increased to 544.50 million
shares from Wednesday's 522.30 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Toshiba was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Semiconductor makers were generally weak after New York's
Nasdaq composite index declined 129.84 points to 4,013.34
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Losers also included steelmakers, the rubber, brokerage and
glass sectors, while the mining, oil and insurance sectors drew
buying.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 738 to 506, with 161 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
