<HEADLINE> China to Hold International Expo on Stamps, Coins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The south China city of
Guangzhou will hold a stamp and coin exhibition on the theme of
Beijing's bid for hosting the 2008 Olympic Games from October 31
through November 3.
</P>
<P>
According to the exhibition's organizing committee, this is the
third time that China has had an international professional
exhibition on stamps and coins after exhibitions in Beijing and
Shanghai in 1995 and 1997, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will have a display space of 8,000 square meters.
Postal and coinage bureaus, stamp and coin dealers from about 50
countries and regions are expected to participate in the
exhibition, including Australia, Germany, France, Italy, United
States and Australia.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 provincial stamp and coin collecting companies
from China will also attend the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition, a variety of cultural activities will be
held for visitors, and many rare stamps and coins will be
auctioned. 
</P>
