<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Supports ASEAN-CER Free Trade Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has backed an
initiative to expand the ASEAN Free Trade Area (AFTA) to cover an
area called Closer Economic Relations between Australia and New
Zealand, or known in short as CER, the Thai News Agency (TNA)
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Thailand will take part in negotiations on the formation of the
so-called AFTA-CER Free Trade Area, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a meeting of the Council of Economic
Ministers this week, which was then endorsed by the cabinet at its
weekly meeting, it said.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN economic ministers discussed the formation of the AFTA-
CER Free Trade Area when they met with their CER counterparts in
Singapore in October last year, aiming to open up trade more
widely with countries outside the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN ministers also agreed to set up a high-level task
force to conduct a feasibility study on the establishment of the
proposed AFTA-CER Free Trade Area and to present results of the
study to the 32nd ASEAN Economic Ministers Meeting, scheduled to
be held here next month.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN now groups Brunei, Cambodia, Indonesia, Laos,
Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and
Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
If results of the study are positive, it is expected that the
proposed ASEAN-CER Free Trade Area will take shape by the year
2010.
</P>
<P>
In case of Thailand, the Ministry of Commerce's Department of
Business Economics had also conducted a study on the proposed plan
and found that, in the dynamic dimension, the newly-expanded free
trade area could enhance Thailand's competitiveness and bargaining
power in the world market, though the country would not gain much
in the static term due to minimal trade so far between Thailand
and the CER, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The study suggested, however, that Thailand and the ASEAN should
not accelerate the implementation of the ASEAN-CER Free Trade Area
if they were not ready.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Ministry study also called for the dissemination of
information on the proposed establishment of the AFTA-CER Free
Trade Area and the opening of a public hearing to gather opinions
of the public on the regional scheme, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000907.0220 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
