JAKARTA -- The United Nations force in East Timor has safely
evacuated 54 humanitarian workers from Atambua, a city of
Indonesia's East Nusa Tenggara province, where four U.N. staff
were killed Wednesday in an attack on the office of the U.N. High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) by East Timor militiamen.
</P>
<P>
