Suai to Atambua immediately after the attack occurred. As of 8:00
p.m., the U.N. staff in Atambua had been evacuated to Dili,
capital of East Timor, while some others were being located to the
East Nusa Tenggara provincial capital of Kupang and other parts of
Indonesia, the Jakarta Post daily Thursday quoted the U.N. office
in Jakarta as saying. Four U.N. staff were killed and one badly
injured when thousands of angry mobs and militiamen attacked and
burned the UNHCR office Wednesday. (UNHCR-evacuated)
