<HEADLINE> Two Arrested in Nanjing for Drug Trafficking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Police in Nanjing, capital of
east China's Jiangsu Province, have arrested two persons who were
trafficking heroin concealed inside their bodies.
</P>
<P>
The arrested two were carrying 182 heroin pills totaling 546
grams in weight, according to local newspaper reports.
</P>
<P>
This is the first such case in Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
On August 30, sources from southwest China's Guizhou Province
informed police at the Lukou Airport in Nanjing that two people
aboard an airplane A-320 that flew from Guiyang to Nanjing, were
smuggling drugs that they had swallowed.
</P>
<P>
The two suspects were, Gu Jiaping, 17, a farmer from Huoqiu
County of Anhui Province, and Yang Biao, 19, from Guangshui City
in central China's Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
Gu and Yang were arrested immediately after the plane landed at
the Lukou Airport at 3:15 pm August 30. They were carrying 101 and
81 heroin pills respectively.
</P>
<P>
Gu and Yang claimed that they were cheated by an employment
advertisement and were forced to swallow the pills.
</P>
<P>
Another drug trafficker in connection with the case has been
arrested at the Guiyang Airport.
</P>
<P>
Further investigation into the case is continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
