<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A 15-year-old student died
today after he was knocked down by a taxi robber Wednesday
afternoon in northeast China's port city of Dalian.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy happened when Geng Chengwen, the victim, and 16
other students were on their way back home at about 4:30 p.m.
Along with Geng's death, several others were wounded during the
incident.
</P>
