<HEADLINE> Philippine Government-MILF Talks Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Moro Islamic Liberation Front(
MILF) peace negotiators failed to appear at the scheduled sixth
round of meeting with their government counterparts in the
southern Philippines Thursday.
</P>
<P>
MILF spokesman Eid Kabalu said they opted not to show up at the
venue of the talks in Cotabato city, Maguindanao Province, as they
have yet to come up with a new set of negotiators after the MILF's
Central Committee disbanded the old group headed by rebel chief
negotiator Aleem Abdulaziz Mimbantas.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the MILF Central Committee headed by chieftain Hashim
Salamat dissolved the peace panel, saying they could not talk
peace with the government while its armed forces are attacking
their camps.
</P>
<P>
With this new development, government chief negotiator Edgado
Batenga said his group could only hope that the MILF would return
to the negotiating table soon for them to resolve the dragging
Mindanao problem.
</P>
<P>
Both the government and MILF declared that they are not closing
their doors for a peaceful solution to the decades-old armed
Mindanao conflict that has already claimed the lives of an
estimated 120,000 people since 1969. 
</P>
</TEXT>
