<HEADLINE> URGENT: Indonesia, IMF Sign New Agreement on Economic Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government and
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) here Thursday signed a new
agreement, called Letter of Intent (LoI), on economic reform
programs in the country.
</P>
<P>
The revised LoI is largely the same as the previous pact signed
by the two on July 31, except for the stipulation of a 10- point
economic recovery program recommended by the new economic team of
the Indonesian government.
</P>
<P>
The LoI has to be approved by the IMF board of directors before
the Fund can disburse a fresh 400 million U.S. dollar loan tranche
to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
IMF representative in Jakarta John Dodsworth said on Wednesday
the IMF is expected to disburse the 400 million dollar loan of its
five billion U.S. dollars bailout fund to Indonesia by the third
week of this month. 
</P>
