<HEADLINE> China Provides Encephalitis Vaccines to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 7 (Xinhua) -- China has provided 500,000
pieces of vaccines to Nepal to combat the widespread encephalitis,
according the Nepali Health Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Ram Baran Yadav said this on Thursday on an
inspection visit to the encephalitis-hit districts in southern
Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Yadav said these vaccines had to be inoculated before the
outbreak of the disease.
</P>
<P>
About 100 people have died of encephalitis in Nepal since the
monsoon season began in mid-June. Of the deceased, 52 are in
southern Terai plain bordering India.
</P>
<P>
People are infected with encephalitis when bitten by a
particular type of gnat, which usually appear during the rainy
season and increase in numbers due to poor conditions. The disease
claims the lives of hundreds of people in Nepal every year.
</P>
