<HEADLINE> Cypriot President Denounces UN Failure to Implement Resolutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Cypriot President
Glafcos Clerides told world leaders on Wednesday that there is no
more obvious example of the UN's failure to carry out resolutions
than the case of Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the three-day U.N. Millennium Summit, which opened
this morning at the U.N. headquarters in New York, Clerides said
the resolutions of the United Nations Security Council must be
respected and implemented.
</P>
<P>
"There is no more flagrant example of this failure in
implementing resolutions adopted by the General Assembly and the
Security Council than the case of Cyprus," the president said.
</P>
<P>
Numerous resolutions " were not implemented for over a quarter
of a century. This failure constitutes nothing less than an
affront to the international community," Clerides said.
</P>
<P>
"We are now engaged in yet another effort to solve the Cyprus
problem. I will participate in the forthcoming negotiations, as
always with good will and determination, to find a just and viable
solution within parameters established by UN resolutions, a
solution that will meet the interests and restore and safeguard
human rights for all Cypriots," he said.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been virtually partitioned since 1974 when troops
from Turkey occupied the north of the island in response to a coup
in Nicosia by the then ruling Greek junta
</P>
<P>
A new round of "proximity talks" is scheduled to begin in New
York on September 12. U.N. resolutions call for Cyprus to become a
bizonal federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
