<HEADLINE> Myanmar Calls for Efforts to Promote Information Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar leader Lieutenant-
General Khin Nyunt Wednesday called for efforts to promote the
country's information sector, especially its radio and television
services, in conformity with the global changes and development.
</P>
<P>
"Only then can Myanmar's objective conditions and correct news
reports be effectively distributed to the global community in time,
"Khin Nyunt, first secretary of the State Peace and Development
Council, was quoted by Thursday's official newspaper The New Light
of Myanmar as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with staff members of the state-run Myanma Radio and
Television (MRTV), Khin Nyunt told them to distribute news reports
on objective situation of Myanmar's various sectors such as
political, economic, social and cultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
He charged that at present, the international information
sector is being dominated and manipulated by some big western
nations,saying that news is being sent in accord with their wish.
</P>
<P>
As a result, he complained that "it is not easy for a
developing nation like Myanmar to inform the world about its true
conditions."
</P>
<P>
He called for efforts to apply various means to distribute
correct news reports of the nation internationally.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the MRTV is arranging to upgrade its radio and TV
machines and equipment, changing its present TV system to digital
system.
</P>
<P>
Radio Myanmar was established in early 1946 and color TV was
made available starting in June 1980. The TV Myanmar is now made
available of transmission of satellite news with the cooperation
of the Cable Network News (CNN) and the Japan Broadcasting
Corporation(NHK). 
