<HEADLINE> Over Half Venezuelans Support Death Penalty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Fifty-one percent of the
Venezuelans back the application of death penalty in this country
to reduce high crime rate, according to soundings by the
Encuestadora Roxon polling firm published on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Forty-four percent is against death penalty and the remaining
five percent did not know or did not want to answer. The poll was
made on August 21-27 with a sampling of 1,400 persons in several
cities.
</P>
<P>
According to the poll, the main concern of 24 million
Venezuelans was insecurity.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-two percent of the people supported life imprisonment as
another punishment, while 43 percent was against and five percent
did not answer.
</P>
