<HEADLINE> Younger Managers Appointed for State Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- First Automobile Works (FAW),
China's largest automobile manufacturer in northeast China's Jilin
Province, appointed a new managing team, reducing the average age
of the managers from 53.6 years old to 47.8.
</P>
<P>
The new FAW managing team is made up of nine members, five less
than the last term, and the new general manager Zhu Yanfeng is 39
years old.
</P>
<P>
Officials said the change in the FAW, a state-owned enterprise,
reflects the government's change of attitude towards the
management structure of such enterprises. The government is making
state-owned enterprises more efficient by using fewer and younger
managers.
</P>
<P>
More young people have been appointed as managers of state
enterprises for their strong sense of competition and creative
ideas in the face of the market economy.  
</P>
</TEXT>
