<HEADLINE> Brazilian Vehicle Sales Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZIL, September 6 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian motor vehicle
industry sold 123,147 cars, trucks and buses in August, an
increase of 12.38 percent over July, the National Association of
Motor Vehicles Manufacturers (Antavea) announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The August sales show a 12.37 percent increase over the same
month of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The accumulated sales so far this year have amounted to 842,638
units, an increase of 15.16 percent over the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The production of vehicles over the first eight months of this
year reached 1,127,750 units, up 24.51 percent from the same
period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The motor vehicle exports in August reached 360 million U.S.
dollars, while the accumulated amount for the whole year was 2.564
billion dollars, up 8.24 percent and 1.68 percent from the same
periods of 1999 respectively. 
</P>
