<HEADLINE> Colombia Detains 14,427 Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- Colombia detained 14,427 drug
traffickers in the first half of this year, increasing by 34
percent against 10,762 in the same period of 1999, according to a
report of the Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The report said the cocaine seized in the first half of 2000
amounted to 37.7 tons, tripling that of the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
It said while the number of army's anti-drug actions increased
sharply during the first half of 2000, the amount of coca leaves
confiscated was 4.5 times bigger than that of the same period of
1999.
</P>
<P>
It said the seizure of cocaine and the confiscation of cocaine
basic paste and coca leaves between January and June in 2000
prevented sales of 48 tons of cocaine to illegal market. "This
cocaine would have produced 1,444 billion dollars for the drug
traffickers," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
