<HEADLINE> Colombian Air Force Destroys Plane of Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, September 6 (Xinhua) -- A rebels' plane with a full
load of ammunition was destroyed by the government air force near
the neutral zone in southern Colombia, said Colombian Air Force (
FAC) commander General Hector Fabio Velasco on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The cargo aircraft, which is said to belong to the rebel
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), was destroyed near
Barrancominas in Guainia department, when it failed in following
the orders of the FAC pilots, said General Velasco.
</P>
<P>
The Air Force commander said that FAC had got intelligence
reports beforehand that the plane would have a mission to
transport ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The pilots in the destroyed plane had tried to get some cover
in the jungle, but it was detected and destroyed with shots, said
General Velasco. 
</P>
