<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Children Compensated after Taking Rat Poison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Two children from Shanghai
received 10,000 yuan and 12,000 yuan in compensation respectively
after accidentally taking rat poison at a restaurant.
</P>
<P>
On May 25 last year, Xu Wenhao, 5, and Zhu Wenjun, 2, together
with their respective parents, went to the Yueyou restaurant for a
meal. Xu and Zhu ate some groundnut kernels they found in a corner
of the dining hall, which turned out to be rat poison.
</P>
<P>
They were soon rushed to a local hospital and escaped danger
after doctors used a gastric lavage on them.
</P>
<P>
Their parents appealed to a local court for a compensation of
over 30,000 yuan from the restaurant, by accusing it of placing
rat poison without a warning, while the restaurant argued that the
parents were irresponsible for not guarding their children.
</P>
<P>
The two sides finally reached an agreement on the compensation
under the mediation of the local court.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
