<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The stocks on the Buenos
Aires Exchange closed up on Wednesday with the leading Merval
index increasing by 0.12 percent to 496.26 points compared with
Tuesday's 496.52 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 48.96 million U.S. dollars against 47.66
million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate fell to 8.05 percent from 8.
50 percent in the 24-hour term. The exchange rate of the Argentine
peso against the U.S. dollar stood at 0.995 for purchase and 1.005
for sale. 
</P>
