<DOCNO> XIE20000907.0304 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Radiation-Preventing Material Distilled From Vegetables </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have
discovered a formula that prevents natural radiation from plants
belonging to the mustard plant family, like radishes and cabbages.
</P>
<P>
The formula, named SP88, was created by scientists at the
Shanghai Institution of Plant Ecophysiology with Chinese Academy
of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
The institution has gained a patent for SP88 and will put it
into mass production soon, an institute source said.
</P>
<P>
Scientists with that institution said SP88 can be widely
applied to various fields, including relieving the radiation from
ionization and electromagnetism, and counteracting the decrease of
leukocyte and thrombocyte during the radiotherapy or chemotherapy.
</P>
<P>
Experiments on calves, mice and fruit flies indicated that SP88
works by restraining the excessive radicals in cells, which damage
big molecules and causes the malfunction of cells.
</P>
<P>
Scientists also validated the function of SP88 by comparing two
groups of wheat seeds growing in a satellite, one was immersed in
SP88 solution and the other in distilled water. It turned out that
the radiation had much less of an ill effect on the former group.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
