<HEADLINE> Union Helps Enhance Education System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Educational
Workers' Union will contribute to the drive to revitalize the
nation through science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The union is an indispensable force in promoting the expansion
of China's education system, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Junjiu, vice-chairman of the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions, said the largest body in the country's education
sector should continue to build up morals, improve skills and
continue educating students.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar to mark the 50th anniversary of the
organization Wednesday in Beijing, Zhang spoke highly of the union
in advancing the country's educational, cultural, economic and
social progress.
</P>
<P>
The union has registered 12.4 million members since it was
founded on August 2, 1950, marking it one of the largest trade
unions in China.
</P>
<P>
Over the past half century, the union has concentrated on
educational reform and development, helped educational workers
have their say and protected the rights of teachers.
</P>
<P>
"With its outstanding achievements and distinct character, the
union has become a mass organization that the workers support and
have faith in," Zhang said.
</P>
<P>
The union is involved in running 97 percent of China's
universities and institutes and 94 percent of its high schools,
according to You Guodong, vice-chairman of the union.  
</P>
