<HEADLINE> London Stock Market Closes Flat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Europe's leading markets except
London performed an about turn Thursday to end the session in
positive territory after spending most of the session in negative
mood.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 index ended flat, propped up by oil firms and
Vodafone Group against heavy losses for Invensys. The index closed
down just 5.5 points or 0.1 percent to 6,689.2.
</P>
<P>
Oil and gas shares helped stem bigger losses on the back of
crude prices, which have vaulted to fresh 10-year highs. Oil
giants BP Amoco and Shell hit record highs before closing up 0.7
percent and 1.6 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Frankfurt's Xetra Dax, rose 40.32 points, or 0.55 percent, to 7,
373.34, with Europe's biggest software company SAP leaping out of
the mire, rising 2 percent, and chip maker Infineon Technologies
added 1.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Paris CAC-40 closed moderately higher after a session
dominated by strong gains in oil stocks and a surge in car maker
Peugeot. The index closed up 0.55 percent or 37.67 points to 6,834.
46. 
