<HEADLINE> Singapore Calls for U.N. Leadership in Multilateral Organizations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Thursday
called on the United Nations to provide leadership within the
community of multilateral organizations to help the poorer nations
develop the capacity to profit from globalization and the
knowledge resolution.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the U.N. Millennium Summit which opened at the U.N.
headquarters in New York Wednesday, Goh Chok Tong, prime minister
of Singapore, said the world is becoming more globalized, yet at
the same time more fragmented.
</P>
<P>
While technological advances have brought the world closer,
they have also opened up divides between those who are able to
cope with the resultant challenges and those who lack the capacity
to do so, the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
"We need to strengthen the United Nations to deal with these
new problems, as well as the stubborn old ones. We need to do so
because no nation can tackle these challenges alone," the prime
minister said.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations, the International Monetary Fund, the World
Bank and several other international institutions were created in
a different era to deal with different challenges, and they must
be updated," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Also today, there is an imperative for them to coordinate
their efforts. They need to get together to assess what
competences the poorer nations need to develop in this new era,"
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
