<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Blue Chips Fall But Tech Stocks Rebound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended
mixed Thursday with blue chips falling on corporate profit
warnings, but the tech stocks bounced back from a selloff in the
previous sessions.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Dow Jones industrial average fell
50.77 at 11,259.87 points, ending a rally in the past four
sessions.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The technology
heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 85.01 at 4,098.35 and the
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 10.26 at 1,502.51.
</P>
<P>
Blue chip stocks fell as several companies warned separately
that their earnings would not meet expectations in the third
quarter because of higher costs and lower demands in the slowing
economy. Among them were DuPont, Campbell Soup, Circuit City
Stores and May Department Stores.
</P>
<P>
The warnings came after the Federal Reserve had raised interest
rates for six times since last summer in an effort to slow the U.
S. economy and keep inflation under control. Higher rates would
hit companies in earnings.
</P>
<P>
Profit-taking also dragged the Dow index lower. Investors took
some money out of the market to lock in profits from a previous
rally.
</P>
<P>
But the tech shares came back after a deep falling Wednesday
and Tuesday. The Nasdaq index fell 220.99 points in the previous
two sessions after analyst downgrades of several prominent tech
companies including Intel and Micron Technology.
</P>
<P>
Chip makers Intel and Micron Technology rose Thursday after
sufferings. Sun Microsystems also moved up, recovering nearly all
of its loss Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 1.03 at 675.49 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 3.03 at 974.18. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies was up 6.50 at 542.82.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-4 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,556 up, 1,306 down and 516
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 973.54 million shares from 992.42
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
